# Search Preferences

Copy this file to `config/search.md` and fill in your preferences.
This file is gitignored — only the .example template is committed.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Remote Preference | Remote or Hybrid |
| Comp Floor | $X base + Y% bonus + $Z equity |
| Company Types | Mission-driven, growth-stage, midsize |
| Companies to Skip | (comma-separated list of companies to exclude) |
| Sources | LinkedIn, Greenhouse, Wellfound, Lever, Ashby |
| Apple Notes Prefix | Job Search |

## Target Role Titles

List the exact titles to search for, one per line:

- Senior Director of Engineering
- VP of Engineering
- Head of Engineering

## Location Constraints

- Remote: Yes
- Hybrid (Austin TX area): Yes
- Relocation required: No
- 100% in-office: No

## Staffing/Aggregator Company Exclusions

These are recruitment platforms, not actual employers. Never use their listings or URLs.
The `scan-email` skill also auto-trashes any inbox message whose sender domain
matches one of the entries in the "trash sender substring" column.

| Name | Trash Sender Substring |
|------|------------------------|
| Lensa | lensa.com |
| Ladders | ladders.com |

## Marketing / Non-Job-Search Senders to Auto-Trash

These are not job alerts and never will be. The `scan-email` skill auto-trashes
them on every run alongside the aggregator list above:

| Sender | Trash Sender Substring |
|--------|------------------------|
| TopResume | topresume.com |
| LinkedIn connection invites | invitations@linkedin.com |
| LinkedIn InMail / sales outreach | hit-reply@linkedin.com |

## Job Alert Senders to Auto-Trash After Scan

These senders *do* have content `scan-email` reads (job postings), but every
individual alert should be trashed once the run is done — otherwise they
accumulate whenever the subject-line classifier, already-seen dedup, age
filter, or other pre-body-fetch filters skip them. Phase 6 runs this trash
pass AFTER metadata scan, body fetch, and user confirmation, so adding a
sender here is safe: content has already been extracted by the time the
trash fires. See issue #86.

| Sender | Trash Sender Substring |
|--------|------------------------|
| LinkedIn job alerts (fit/role) | jobalerts-noreply@linkedin.com |
| LinkedIn job alerts (daily digest) | jobs-noreply@linkedin.com |
| LinkedIn job alerts (recommendation) | jobs-listings@linkedin.com |

